President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Terrence M. Andrews of California to serve as a Judge on the United States Court of Federal Claims. Andrews currently serves as Staff Director and Chief Counsel to the United States Senate Committee on Indian Affairs. He has previously held positions in the Department of Housing and Urban Development, the Department of Homeland Security, and served as the General Counsel and Chief Prosecutor for the Pascua Yaqui Indian Tribe. Andrews holds a B.A. from Morgan State University, an M.A. from Salve Regina University, a J.D. from Roger Williams University School of Law, and an L.L.M. from George Washington University School of Law.